eren Schutz als der Ausbau der Aufsichtsbehörden.  aThis book addresses the legal background of the derivative business. The author analyses existing rules and comes to the conclusion that further regulation is superfluous. The European legal systems are aware of substantiated principles that are applicable to this type of business, such as those from the insurance and gambling fields. Established instruments of the law of obligations and criminal law offer better protection than the mere expansion of supervisory authorities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDerivative securitiesxLaw and legislation. 0aDerivatives (Mathematics) 0aDerivatives (Mathematics). 4aDerivat (Wertpapier). 70(DE-588)4065682-20(DE-627)1061177930(DE-576)209159944aWertpapierrecht2gnd 70(DE-588)4381572-80(DE-627)1865955490(DE-576)211843865aDerivatgWertpapier2gnd 7aLAW / Banking.2bisacsh  aDerivatives (Share).1 aRoberts, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2010z9783110233629oZDB-23-DGC0 cprintz978389949805940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978389949806640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783899498066423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783899498066/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2010  aZDB-23-DGGb2010  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014